{"key":"processedPost-10045908","value":{"id":10045908,"first":10007638,"last":10046795,"when":1238094728,"utime":"03/26/09 10:12 PM","content":"The foil needs to be there.&nbsp; Make sure you're using squares of foil that only protect the cake from trying to colonize the perlite.&nbsp; Don't let the foil cover the whole surface.<br /><br />Another tip is to use your fingers to 'rake' the perlite so it has lots of ridges and an irregular surface.&nbsp; This greatly increases the surface area, giving more humidity.&nbsp; Also make sure when you mist that the overspray covers the perlite, re-moistening it.<br /><br />For now, pile a tablespoon or so of vermiculte on each cake and soak it well.&nbsp; This will hydrate your cakes from the top down and supply water for the current flush.<br />RR","title":"Re: shotgun terrarium humidity"}}